  </datafield>
  <datafield tag="520" ind1=" " ind2=" ">
    <subfield code="a">We undertake a theoretical study of edge spin-vortex excitations in fractional quantum Hall fluid. This is done in view of quantised Euler hydrodynamics theory. The dispersions of true excitations for fractions within <math altimg="si1.gif" display="inline" overflow="scroll"><mn>0</mn><mo>≤</mo><mi>ν</mi><mo>≤</mo><mn>1</mn></math> are simulated which exhibit universal similarities and differences in behaviour. The differences arise from different edge smoothness and spin (pseudo-spin) polarisations, in addition to spin-charge competition. In particular, tuning the spin-charge factor causes coherent spin flipping associated with partial and total polarisations of edge spin-vortices. This observation is tipped as an ideal mechanism for realisation of functional spintronic devices.</subfield>
